<define-tag pagetitle>Debian Installer Jessie RC 2 release</define-tag>
<define-tag release_date>2015-03-27</define-tag>
#use wml::debian::news

<p>
The Debian Installer <a
href="https://wiki.debian.org/DebianInstaller/Team">team</a> is pleased to
announce the second release candidate of the installer for Debian 8
<q>Jessie</q>.
</p>


<h2>Improvements in this release of the installer</h2>

<ul>
  <li>brltty-udeb:
    <ul>
      <li>Make grub beep at boot when brltty was used during installation (#774536).</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>console-setup:
    <ul>
      <li>Fix default keymap/layout for several languages.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>debian-installer:
    <ul>
      <li>Keep track of more packages in Built-Using (#696418, #700026).</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>libdebian-installer:
    <ul>
      <li>Fix possible segfault on armel/armhf (#776488).</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>systemd:
    <ul>
      <li>Enable tty 2 to 6 even when dbus is not installed (#772700).</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>tasksel:
    <ul>
      <li>Remove pm-utils from the desktop and laptop tasks.</li>
      <li>Remove libgl1-mesa-dri from the desktop task.</li>
      <li>When a desktop is preseeded, only enable that desktop (#771576).</li>
      <li>Also install libreoffice-gtk along gnome-orca, to make LibreOffice accessible (#773763).</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>


<h2>Hardware support changes</h2>

<ul>
  <li>debian-installer:
    <ul>
      <li>Provide u-boot binaries for armhf systems without u-boot in flash.</li>
      <li>Add a workaround for the console baudrate mismatch on some i.MX6-based systems.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>debian-installer, network-console, oldsys-preseed:
    <ul>
      <li>Add support for Buffalo Linkstation LS-CHLv2/LS-XHL (#744714, #744715, #744716).</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>grub2:
    <ul>
      <li>Add support for running a 64-bit Linux kernel on a 32-bit EFI (#775202).</li>
      <li>Fix UEFI boot failure with some firmware that returns incorrect paths (#735960).</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>linux:
    <ul>
      <li>[armhf] Add support for OMAP5432 uEVM (#772953).</li>
      <li>[arhmf] Add device-tree for LinkSprite pcDuino V3 (#774067).</li>
      <li>[arm64] Ensure efivars and efi-pstore are loaded on EFI systems (#773309).</li>
      <li>udeb: Add i2c-designware-{core,platform} to i2c-modules and i2c-hid to input-modules (#772578).</li>
      <li>[amd64] Enable EFI_MIXED to support Bay Trail systems.</li>
      <li>efi: Expose underlying UEFI firmware platform size to userland, to support installation on Bay Trail systems (#775191).</li>
      <li>Add support for Bananapro board (#779311).</li>
      <li>[armhf] Add DTB for Olimex A20-OLinuXino-LIME2 (#777455).</li>
      <li>[armhf] Enable CONFIG_BACKLIGHT_GPIO as a module (#778783).</li>
      <li>[armhf] Enable FB_SIMPLE on sunxi platform, backporting fixes and DTS entries.</li>
      <li>[x86] ACPI / video: Add disable_native_backlight quirk for various Samsung models and Dell XPS15 L521X (#772440).</li>
      <li>[x86] ALSA: Enable SND_SOC, SND_SOC_INTEL_SST, SND_SOC_INTEL_HASWELL_MACH, SND_SOC_INTEL_BYT_RT5640_MACH, SND_SOC_INTEL_BYT_MAX98090_MACH as modules (#773835).</li>
      <li>arcmsr: Backport changes up to Linux 3.18 (#698821).</li>
      <li>drm: Enable DRM_BOCHS, DRM_QXL as modules (qxl disabled by default but can be forced with modeset=1).</li>
      <li>Add support for Bananapro board (#779311).</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>u-boot:
    <ul>
      <li>Backport support for the LeMaker Banana Pro board (#779908).</li>
      <li>Backport support for A20-OLinuXino-LIME2 (#777466).</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>


<h2>Localization status</h2>

<ul>
  <li>75 languages are supported in this release.</li>
  <li>Full translation for 19 of them.</li>
</ul>


<h2>Known issues in this release</h2>

<p>
See the <a href="$(DEVEL)/debian-installer/errata">errata</a> for details and a
full list of known issues.
</p>


<h2>Feedback for this release</h2>

<p>
We need your help to find bugs and further improve the installer, so please
try it. Installer CDs, other media and everything else you will need are
available at our <a href="$(DEVEL)/debian-installer">web site</a>.
</p>


<h2>Thanks</h2>

<p>
The Debian Installer team thanks everybody who has contributed to this
release.
</p>
